<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/9788> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #9788" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Son of the jurist, perhaps a senator in 43. Cicero attributes his absence from the meeting of the Senate in honor of his father to grief (Phil. 9.12). He may have survived Philippi, and continued as husband of Messalla's sister, father of the poetess Sulpicia, and himself a poet (Jerome, Adv. Iovin. 1.46, from Seneca, De matrimonio, ed. Haase 3, p. 432, 77; Hor. Sat. 1.10.85-86; Ovid Trist. 2.441; Plin. Ep. 5.3.5). (RS, MS-RP 1.289-290)" .
